===Etymology 1===
Fusion of {{inh|en|enm|redden||to deliver from, rid, clear}} (from {{inh|en|ang|hreddan||to deliver, rescue, free from, take away}}, from  {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*hraddjan}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*hradjaną||to save, deliver}}) and {{inh|en|enm|ridden||to clear away, remove obstructions}} (from {{inh|en|ang|ġeryddan|t=to clear land}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*riudijaną||to clear}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*rewdʰ-||to clear land}}.

Akin to {{cog|ofs|hredda||to save}}, {{cog|nl|redden||to save, deliver}}, {{cog|de|retten||to save, deliver}}, {{m|de|roden||to clear}} and {{m|de|reuten||to clear}}, {{cog|non|ryðja||to clear, empty}}, {{cog|non|hróðja|hrōðja|to clear, strip}}. More at {{m|en|redd}}.

